The paper discusses the creation, manipulation, storage, and distribution of challenges for digital forensics education and training, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The system also relies on the use of base disk images and the emulation of desired activities, which could be considered as aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of the system for tool testing and validation, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE) and information theory (cs.IT).
